what platforms does webauth support stanford answers stanford university stanford answers what platforms does webauth support categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home what platforms does webauth support search this site the primary target platforms for webauth development are solaris and linux but the code should be portable to any unix system the modules make extensive use of apache 2.0 s apr libraries for portability it has been successfully built on mac os x 10.2 with a locally built openssl since the version that comes with 10.2 was still too old to support webauth webauth also builds on aix 5.2 including the ldap module once cyrus sasl has been ported to that system the primary portability constraint is likely the support libraries that webauth needs for basic authentication only openssl curl and mit kerberos or heimdal are required which are all very portable the ldap lookup code however requires openldap and cyrus sasl and the latter may be difficult to get working on unusual platforms particularly platforms with unusual shared library handling if you have ported webauth to a new platform and had to make code changes to get it to compile we would be very interested in the changes needed please post your patches to the webauth info mailing list for more information see the stanford webauth page linux at stanford unix systems software webauth stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
